## ⚠️ Supabase Free Tier — What You're Up Against

Before the issue list, you need to understand what free tier actually means for performance:

| Limitation | Free Tier | Impact |
|---|---|---|
| **Auto-pause** | Database pauses after **7 days of inactivity** | First request after pause takes **10–30 seconds** |
| **Compute** | Shared micro instance (0.25 vCPU) | Slow query execution, no parallelism guarantee |
| **Connections** | ~60 pooled connections shared globally | Hitting limits causes `ECONNREFUSED` |
| **Region** | `aws-0-ap-northeast-1` (Tokyo) | ~80–200ms RTT from Pakistan/Europe |
| **No read replicas** | Single instance for all reads + writes | No load distribution |
| **Row limits** | 500 MB storage | N/A for now but worth monitoring |

> [!CAUTION]
> **The auto-pause alone can make your site appear completely broken.** If nobody visits for 7 days, the next visitor will stare at a loading screen for 10–30 seconds while Supabase wakes the database up. This is the most commonly reported "site is slow/down" complaint for free tier projects.

