## 🔴 CRITICAL ISSUES

### 1. 🆕 Supabase Free Tier Auto-Pause — The Silent Killer

**What's happening:** Supabase **automatically pauses free-tier databases** after 1 week of inactivity. When paused:
- Your app's `pg.Pool` tries to connect
- The database takes **10–30 seconds to cold-boot**
- During this time, every incoming request hangs or times out
- Users see a blank page or "Loading..." indefinitely

This single issue is likely responsible for the majority of "site is completely broken" reports.

**How to detect it:** Go to your [Supabase dashboard](https://supabase.com/dashboard) → your project → check if it shows a "Paused" badge.

**Fixes (in order of preference):**

**Option A — Upgrade to Supabase Pro ($25/mo):** Auto-pause is disabled. Best long-term solution.

**Option B — Keep a database alive with a cron ping (Free):**  
Set up a cron job (on Hostinger or using cron-job.org) to hit a lightweight health endpoint every 3 days:

```ts
// src/app/api/health/route.ts  ← add this file
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";
import { prisma } from "@/lib/prisma";

export const dynamic = "force-dynamic";

export async function GET() {
  try {
    await prisma.$queryRaw`SELECT 1`;
    return NextResponse.json({ status: "ok" });
  } catch (e) {
    return NextResponse.json({ status: "error" }, { status: 500 });
  }
}
```

Then schedule `GET https://yoursite.com/api/health` every **3 days** via [cron-job.org](https://cron-job.org) (free).

**Option C — Move to Neon (better free tier for Next.js):**  
[Neon](https://neon.tech) offers a free tier with **auto-suspend** (not auto-pause) — it wakes in **~200ms** instead of 10–30 seconds. It's Prisma-compatible and significantly better for this use case.

