### 5. Admin Dashboard: 7 Queries That Serialize Due to Pool Limit

**File:** [`admin/page.tsx`](file:///f:/PROJECTS/wayfindsolutions/src/app/admin/page.tsx#L5-L13)

```ts
await Promise.all([
  prisma.service.count(),
  prisma.portfolioProject.count(),
  prisma.blogPost.count(),
  // ... 7 total
]);
```

`Promise.all` *intends* parallelism, but with `max: 1` these run serially: `7 queries × ~150ms Tokyo RTT = ~1050ms` just for the dashboard stats widget.

**Fix:** Raising pool to `max: 3` (Issue #4) lets 3 run at a time, cutting this to ~2 rounds = ~300ms. Also consider combining into a single raw query:

```ts
const stats = await prisma.$queryRaw`
  SELECT
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM "Service") as services,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM "PortfolioProject") as projects,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM "BlogPost") as posts,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM "TeamMember") as team_members,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM "Testimonial") as testimonials,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM "ContactSubmission") as submissions
`;
```

This replaces 7 round-trips with **1 single query** — the most impactful 5-minute fix for the admin side.

