### 7. All Admin Pages Use Client-Side Waterfall Fetching

**Files:** Every file under `src/app/admin/*/page.tsx`

```tsx
"use client";
useEffect(() => {
  fetch("/api/admin/homepage/hero")   // ← extra HTTP round-trip + DB query
    .then(r => r.json())
    .then(setData);
}, []);

if (!data) return <div>Loading...</div>; // shown every time
```

Every admin page visit does: render blank → hydrate → fetch API → fetch DB → render content. That's a 3-step waterfall, each step adding latency on top of the already-slow free-tier DB.

**Fix:** Server Components with direct Prisma queries (eliminating the extra HTTP hop):

```tsx
// No "use client" on the page itself
import { getSession } from "@/lib/auth";
import { redirect } from "next/navigation";
import { prisma } from "@/lib/prisma";

export default async function HeroPage() {
  const session = await getSession();
  if (!session) redirect("/admin/login");
  
  const data = await prisma.homepageHero.findUnique({ where: { id: "hero" } });
  return <HeroForm initialData={data} />; // "use client" only here
}
```

